norepo: the executable service lives under `SPIN/styx-api`, while `SEED/` and `SPEC/` describe the intended product contract, restart/rebuild goals, and release governance.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:7:The public design intent is contract-first. `POST /v1/contract` is positioned as the universal external interface, while the older envelope-style endpoints remain available for direct compute and diagnostics. Current target versioning is consistently documented as `3.0.0`.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:16:- `SPIN/docs/`: contract artifact and operating docs.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:18:- `handover/`: existing handover/output area in the source repo.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:23:- `app/contract_v1/`: contract-first endpoint, models, dispatcher, handlers, and response builders.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:28:- `tests/`: API, contract, smoke, and fixture coverage.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:47:1. `app/main.py` handles envelope endpoints and wires middleware, exception handling, and the contract router.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:48:2. `app/contract_v1/` implements the universal request/response flow:\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:49:   - `router.py` exposes `POST /v1/contract`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:50:   - `dispatcher.py` loads `SPIN/docs/contract.json`, validates required paths, and routes by intent\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:51:   - `intent_handlers.py` maps contract intents to compute functions\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:52:   - `responses.py` returns the contract response envelope\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:80:This version is reused for both `metadata.styx_version` in contract responses and `meta.api_version` in envelope responses.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:95:- mounts the contract router\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:124:- `POST /v1/contract`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:126:  - supported intents from `SPIN/docs/contract.json`:\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:127:    - `contract`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:147:- `/v1/contract` validates required dotted paths from `SPIN/docs/contract.json` before handler dispatch.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:149:  - contract returns `status=error` with contract-specific error payloads\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:191:- `SPIN/docs/contract.json`: source-of-truth contract artifact\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:217:`.github/workflows/ci.yml` only checks out the repo and runs `echo \"ci ok\"`. This means the repository currently has almost no automated protection around installability, tests, contract drift, or runtime health.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:235:- `tests/test_contract_v1.py`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:236:  - contract OpenAPI schema presence\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:247:- Contract fixtures live under `tests/fixtures/contract_v1/`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:280:- `SPIN/docs/contract.json` is treated as the contract source of truth\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:327:2. Replace the placeholder GitHub Action with at least editable install plus `pytest -q tests/test_contract_v1.py tests/test_smoke.py`.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:332:7. Audit contract and envelope feature parity regularly, because both surfaces currently evolve in parallel.\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:338:- Contract layer: `SPIN/styx-api/app/contract_v1/`\n./SEED/styx-analysis-handover.md:341:- Contract artifact: `SPIN/docs/contract.json`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
